# FHEVM Development Guidelines

## Core Requirements

### Smart Contract Development
- **MANDATORY**: All smart contracts MUST use full FHEVM capabilities - no simplified fallbacks allowed
- Smart contracts MUST be developed in [fhevm-hardhat-template](mdc:fhevm-hardhat-template) directory
- Use FHEVM-provided randomness generation methods when randomness is required
- Reference [Fhevm0.8_Reference.md](mdc:Fhevm0.8_Reference.md) for FHEVM contract implementation details

### Frontend Development
- Create new frontend projects in a separate root-level directory
- The [frontend](mdc:frontend) directory is READ-ONLY reference material - do not modify
- Frontend interactions with FHEVM contracts MUST use:
  - `@zama-fhe/relayer-sdk` for real relayer services, OR
  - `@fhevm/mock-utils` for local mock implementation
- Follow interaction patterns from reference frontend when implementing relayer/mock utilities

### UI/UX Standards
- Design modern, beautiful interfaces using styles like:
  - Material Design
  - Minimalist/modern
  - Dark mode support
  - Card-based layouts
  - Neumorphism
- Support bilingual (Chinese/English) interfaces when possible
- Prioritize excellent user experience

### Documentation Policy
- Do NOT create documentation files unless explicitly requested by user
- No automatic README.md or other .md file generation